Quote: "Wowser" is a word unique to New Zealand and Australia. It is a word rapidly passing into extinction, because the type of person it describes - someone who is implacably opposed to alcohol and, by implication, to hedonistic indulgence of any kind - is also dying out. As the once-powerful temperance movement fades into history and a new generation of New Zealanders grows up accustomed to the civilised pleasures of a deregulated liquor industry, "wowser" is a word that seems to belong in the 50s.
