Date: 0/0/1916
Source: Wowser, The
Author: THORNTON
Vol / Page: 8
Edition:
Quote: Wowser is a term somewhat indefinite in its application and meaning. The following definitions given to the author by bushmen themselves may help the reader to understand what a Colonial means when he uses the word. It may mean:- 1) `A man who tries to rob a bloke of his beer and pleasure' - therefore especially applicable to the temperance reformer.2) `A bloke who wears out the knees of his pants on Sundays praying, and another part of his pants all the week backsliding' - i.e. a hypocrite. 3) `Any sky-pilot, priest, or local preacher who makes a bloke uncomfortable, and pretends to be religious.'
