Date: 0/0/1921
Source: At The Front
Author: FOSTON
Vol / Page: 123
Edition:
Quote: <i>Wowser</i>: The word, it is understood, was derived from a Chinese term, meaning a man of probity and character; but he had seen it stated that the word was a corruption of `rouser'. However, neither definition worried him, because it was the sneer now implied that he proposed to deal with. According to opponents, the `wowser' was the most objectionable person in the world.
